<h1>Latest news 08-03-2025</h1>

 <h2>NuTyX 25.04.2 available with cards 3.2.1</h2>
  <p>
   Spiky and me are happy to announce the new version of NuTyX 25.04.2 and cards 3.2.1 .
 <h2>What's new</h2>
  <h3>2 separated init systems</h3>
   <p>
    From now on, init system are separated.
    One set of ISOs is available in each init system. 
  <h3>Cards 3.0</h3>
   <p>
    A year of development will have been necessary.
   <p>
    No new runtime dependencies for cards.
   <p>
    Packages are now signed with the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EdDSA#Ed25519">ED25519 EdDSA algorithm</a>.
   <p>
 Hash is now via SHA512 instead of MD5Sum.
   <p>
 The archive name of a package is now easier to read.
   <p>
 The /etc/cards.conf configuration file has been simplified.
   <p>
 New commands (cards functions) are introduced:
 <ul>
 <li>
 cards repo for metadata verification/generation
 <li>
 cards dependent for displaying a package's reverse dependencies
 <li> 
 cards key for generating the key pair for signing packages
 </ul>
 <p>
 Existing commands have been improved:
     <ul>
      <li>
       cards search allows search in package names only
      <li>
       cards files and cards query allows search in installed packages AND in repositories
      <li>
       cards diff displays all necessary information on package validity.
      <li>
       cards info displays new info such as signature, hash sum, dependencies
      <li>
       mybld command has been completely redesigned and requires much less time to perform tasks.
     </ul>
  <p>
   The cards deprecate and cards base commands have been removed.
  <p>
   The package building process is now done exclusively in an isolated NuTyX.
    The 'mybld' command now automatically checks for faulty dynamic links.
  <p>
   You will find all the details on the website, on https://github.com/NuTyX/cards
   and in the Changelog file of cards.doc package.

